{
  "stem": "18778.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But we just went into the shelter.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Mostly, the men stayed outside, unless it got serious and the bombing got close.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then they would all jump into the shelter also.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so we never slept in a bed, for three months, for a whole night, my mother and I.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, I remember a family, Heiman, from Cologne, across the hall from us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they had a daughter, Susan.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, the other family from the St.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Louis was actually one of the committee gentlemen with his family, a lawyer by the name of Houstopfer, with his wife and daughter, and they lived downstairs.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then there was a Hungarian lady.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Her first name was Bergi.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, and I don't remember the Polish opera singer's name or the Irish ladies upstairs, but those are the names I do remember.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And also, one of the more humorous aspects was that the opera singer never paid his rent on time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so regularly, the landlady came and threw his belongings, in a suitcase, down the steps.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he would call the police, and they wouldn't come because they were tired of it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was-- it was a, a comic situation among some very serious business.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And meanwhile, my mother ran down the doors of the various offices of the government to try and get my father processed so we could leave.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she-- she managed it, and he was brought to London under guard of Scotland Yard, like a criminal.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They saw each other from across the street.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think he managed to slip her a note.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, and then we-- I don't remember the exact date when we then trained for Glasgow, but it was an overnight ride.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
